headline: Trump Targets Corporate America to Achieve Economic and Foreign Policy Goals
summary: It wasn’t even broached during his first administration.  Trump, backed by his team of Wall Street financiers, took the unprecedented step of seeking to collect a portion of money generated from sales of AI chips to China by Nvidia Corp. and Advanced Micro Devices Inc. And in a move that could see the US government become Intel Corp.’s largest shareholder, the administration is said to be in talks for taking a 10% stake in the beleaguered chipmaker.
